menu "Watcher Animation Service"

    config WATCHER_ANIM_FPS
        int "Animation frame rate (FPS)"
        default 10
        range 1 60
        help
            Target playback rate for the SD-backed animation streamer.
            Default 10fps balances smoothness with tighter ring-buffer safety.

    config WATCHER_ANIM_RING_FRAMES
        int "Animation ring buffer frames"
        default 4
        range 2 6
        help
            Number of decoded RGB565 frames kept in RAM for the active animation.
            Four frames provide deadline headroom for active playback while a
            second four-frame allocation is shared by staging and prefetch.

    config WATCHER_ANIM_ACTIVE_LOW_WATER_FRAMES
        int "Active playback low-water frames"
        default 1
        range 1 5
        help
            Prioritize active playback reads when its buffered frame count is
            at or below this threshold. The runtime clamps this value to the
            configured ring depth.

    config WATCHER_ANIM_STAGING_PREFILL_FRAMES
        int "Staging switch prefill frames"
        default 2
        range 1 6
        help
            Frames prepared for a staging animation before its first frame is
            committed. The runtime clamps this value to the staging ring depth.

    config WATCHER_ANIM_PREPARE_STALL_TIMEOUT_MS
        int "Animation prepare stall watchdog (ms)"
        default 2000
        range 100 10000
        help
            Failure watchdog for a staging request that makes no open/read
            progress. Expiry emits FAILED(PREPARE_STALLED); it never advances
            normal playback or pretends the request completed.

    config WATCHER_ANIM_DEBUG_PERF
        bool "Enable animation performance logging"
        default n
        help
            Log actual FPS and frame switching latency every 30 frames.
            Useful for debugging animation performance issues.

endmenu
